HEADWORD: Orthopoda
<hw>Or*thop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Ortho-</er>, and <er>-poda</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extinct order of reptiles which stood erect
on the hind legs, and resembled birds in the structure of the feet,
pelvis, and other parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orthopraxy</ent>⟦br⟧
